(7, 1, '2015-08-12 13:00:45', '2015-08-12 11:00:45', '                <h1>For Health Care Executive </h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>Through the efficiencies of producing products based upon an open-source framework, systems can be created in a reliable and cost-effective manner, providing high-quality infrastructure solutions at a fraction of the cost of proprietary development from scratch.  Thus, OHIF system can become the backbone for imaging applications across the health care system, providing Health Care Executives with a viable alternative to premium-cost vendor solutions.  In addition, with the open-source framework of OHIF systems, the Health Care Executive can utilize intellectual property and developer resources within their enterprise to customize OHIF systems through the open developer API, in ways not possible with closed-proprietary vendor systems.</p>\r\n\r\n           \r\n                <form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_blank">\r\n                    <input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_s-xclick">\r\n                    <input type="hidden" name="hosted_button_id" value="NQXLPHWKCY4CC">\r\n                    <button type="submit" class="button large orange-bg radius">Donate OHIF</button>\r\n                    <img alt="" border="0" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif" width="1" height="1">\r\n                </form>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/contact">Contact us</a>', 'For Health Care Executive', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'for-health-care-executive', '', '', '2015-08-20 12:37:00', '2015-08-20 10:37:00', '', 0, 'http://ohif.local/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(8, 1, '2015-08-12 13:00:45', '2015-08-12 11:00:45', '                <h1>For Health Care Executive </h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>Through the efficiencies of producing products based upon an open-source framework, systems can be created in a reliable and cost-effective manner, providing high-quality infrastructure solutions at a fraction of the cost of proprietary development from scratch.  Thus, OHIF system can become the backbone for imaging applications across the health care system, providing Health Care Executives with a viable alternative to premium-cost vendor solutions.  In addition, with the open-source framework of OHIF systems, the Health Care Executive can utilize intellectual property and developer resources within their enterprise to customize OHIF systems through the open developer API, in ways not possible with closed-proprietary vendor systems.</p>\r\n\r\n                <a href="contact.php" class="button large orange-bg radius">Donate OHIF</a>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="contact.php">Contact us</a>', 'For Health Care Executive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-12 13:00:45', '2015-08-12 11:00:45', '', 7, 'http://ohif.local/index.php/2015/08/12/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(9, 1, '2015-08-12 13:02:32', '2015-08-12 11:02:32', '                <h1>For Radiologist</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>The OHIF Zero-footprint web based diagnostic workstation intends to fill the need for a truly open, fully featured image review and analysis tool that is compliant with standardized diagnostic workstation functionality according to IHE BIR (Basic Image Review) profile. Most diagnostic workstations currently available are commercially closed source and share many of the same shortcomings:</p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Complexity due to the need to support multiple clinical scenarios</li>\r\n                    <li>Long development cycles</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require installable clients</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require specific computing hardware</li>\r\n                    <li>Most do not provide interoperability with other vendors</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n                <p>OHIF’s approach is a fully open-source, standards compliant platform for diagnostic interpretation, that is modular and extensible enough to support other specific interpretation workflows such as quality assurance, point-of-care visualization, research and teaching. It is expected to have minimal hardware requirements which will allow it to be deployed in underprivileged regions of the world in an fast, cost-efficient way.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>For radiologists, apart from being a best-of-breed image interpretation tool, the OHIF components can be used as a modular platform to test new interaction paradigms for image review, annotation and analysis, drawing from well established and tested best practices in web interaction that come naturally to modern users.</p>\r\n\r\n                <a href="/contact" class="button large orange-bg radius">Spread the word</a>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/contact">Request specific feature</a>', 'For Radiologist', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'for-radiologists', '', '', '2015-08-20 12:38:52', '2015-08-20 10:38:52', '', 0, 'http://ohif.local/?page_id=9', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(10, 1, '2015-08-12 13:02:32', '2015-08-12 11:02:32', '                <h1>For Radiologist</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>The OHIF Zero-footprint web based diagnostic workstation intends to fill the need for a truly open, fully featured image review and analysis tool that is compliant with standardized diagnostic workstation functionality according to IHE BIR (Basic Image Review) profile. Most diagnostic workstations currently available are commercially closed source and share many of the same shortcomings:</p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Complexity due to the need to support multiple clinical scenarios</li>\r\n                    <li>Long development cycles</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require installable clients</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require specific computing hardware</li>\r\n                    <li>Most do not provide interoperability with other vendors</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n                <p>OHIF’s approach is a fully open-source, standards compliant platform for diagnostic interpretation, that is modular and extensible enough to support other specific interpretation workflows such as quality assurance, point-of-care visualization, research and teaching. It is expected to have minimal hardware requirements which will allow it to be deployed in underprivileged regions of the world in an fast, cost-efficient way.</p>\r\n\r\n                <p>For radiologists, apart from being a best-of-breed image interpretation tool, the OHIF components can be used as a modular platform to test new interaction paradigms for image review, annotation and analysis, drawing from well established and tested best practices in web interaction that come naturally to modern users.</p>\r\n\r\n                <a href="contact.php" class="button large orange-bg radius">Spread the word</a>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="contact.php">Request specific feature</a>', 'For Radiologist', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-12 13:02:32', '2015-08-12 11:02:32', '', 9, 'http://ohif.local/index.php/2015/08/12/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(11, 1, '2015-08-12 13:03:33', '2015-08-12 11:03:33', '                <h1>For Imaging Professional</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>The OHIF Zero-footprint web based diagnostic workstation fills the need for a truly open, fully featured image review and analysis tool that is compliant with standardized diagnostic workstation functionality according to IHE BIR (Basic Image Review) profile. Most diagnostic workstations currently available are commercially closed source and share many of the same shortcomings:\r\n                </p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Complexity due to the need to support multiple clinical scenarios</li>\r\n                    <li>Long development cycles</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require installable clients</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require specific computing hardware</li>\r\n                    <li>Most do not provide interoperability with other vendors</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n                <p>OHIF’s approach is a fully open-source, standards compliant platform for diagnostic interpretation, that is modular and extensible enough to support other specific interpretation workflows such as quality assurance, point-of-care visualization, research and teaching. It is expected to have minimal hardware requirements which will allow it to be deployed in underprivileged regions of the world in an fast, cost-efficient way.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <a href="https://github.com/OHIF" target="_blank" class="button large orange-bg radius">Visit our GitHub page</a>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/forum">Visit forum</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/contact">Contact us</a>\r\n', 'For Imaging Professional', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'for-imaging-pro', '', '', '2015-08-20 12:41:47', '2015-08-20 10:41:47', '', 0, 'http://ohif.local/?page_id=11', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(12, 1, '2015-08-12 13:03:33', '2015-08-12 11:03:33', '                <h1>For Imaging Professional</h1>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <p>The OHIF Zero-footprint web based diagnostic workstation fills the need for a truly open, fully featured image review and analysis tool that is compliant with standardized diagnostic workstation functionality according to IHE BIR (Basic Image Review) profile. Most diagnostic workstations currently available are commercially closed source and share many of the same shortcomings:\r\n                </p>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Complexity due to the need to support multiple clinical scenarios</li>\r\n                    <li>Long development cycles</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require installable clients</li>\r\n                    <li>Many require specific computing hardware</li>\r\n                    <li>Most do not provide interoperability with other vendors</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n                <p>OHIF’s approach is a fully open-source, standards compliant platform for diagnostic interpretation, that is modular and extensible enough to support other specific interpretation workflows such as quality assurance, point-of-care visualization, research and teaching. It is expected to have minimal hardware requirements which will allow it to be deployed in underprivileged regions of the world in an fast, cost-efficient way.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <a href="https://github.com/OHIF" target="_blank" class="button large orange-bg radius">Visit our GitHub page</a>\r\n\r\n                &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/forum">Visit forum</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="contact.php">Contact us</a>\r\n', 'For Imaging Professional', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-12 13:03:33', '2015-08-12 11:03:33', '', 11, 'http://ohif.local/index.php/2015/08/12/11-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(13, 1, '2015-08-12 13:17:33', '2015-08-12 11:17:33', '                <h1>What is the OHIF</h1>\r\n                <p>Open Health Imaging Foundation, a US 501(c)(3) non-profit corporation, provides organizational, legal, and financial support for a broad range of open source software projects. The Foundation provides an established framework for intellectual property, financial contributions and regulatory guidance that simultaneously limits potential legal exposure for our project committers. Through a collaborative and meritocratic development process, OHIF™ projects deliver enterprise-grade, freely available software products that attract active communities of users.  OHIF uses BSD License makes it easy for all users, commercial and individual, to deploy OHIF products.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n                <h3>Mission for OHIF</h3>\r\n                <p>The mission of the Open Health Imaging Foundation (OHIF) is to provide software for the public good. We do this by providing services and support for many like-minded software project communities of individuals.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n                <h3>Founding Members: (alphabetically)</h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Chris Hafey</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Gordon Harris</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Luke Huang</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Rob Lewis</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Armin Moehrle</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Jim Philbin</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Simon Rascovsky</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Wyatt Tellis</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Manabu Tokunaga</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Suresh Viswanathan</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <h3>Founding Organizations: (alphabetically)</h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Barco</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Lury</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Medken</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Radical Imaging</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Raster Images</li>\r\n                </ul>', 'About us', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2015-08-12 13:17:33', '2015-08-12 11:17:33', '', 0, 'http://ohif.local/?page_id=13', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(14, 1, '2015-08-12 13:17:33', '2015-08-12 11:17:33', '                <h1>What is the OHIF</h1>\r\n                <p>Open Health Imaging Foundation, a US 501(c)(3) non-profit corporation, provides organizational, legal, and financial support for a broad range of open source software projects. The Foundation provides an established framework for intellectual property, financial contributions and regulatory guidance that simultaneously limits potential legal exposure for our project committers. Through a collaborative and meritocratic development process, OHIF™ projects deliver enterprise-grade, freely available software products that attract active communities of users.  OHIF uses BSD License makes it easy for all users, commercial and individual, to deploy OHIF products.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n                <h3>Mission for OHIF</h3>\r\n                <p>The mission of the Open Health Imaging Foundation (OHIF) is to provide software for the public good. We do this by providing services and support for many like-minded software project communities of individuals.\r\n                </p>\r\n\r\n                <h3>Founding Members: (alphabetically)</h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Chris Hafey</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Gordon Harris</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Luke Huang</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Rob Lewis</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Armin Moehrle</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Jim Philbin</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Simon Rascovsky</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Wyatt Tellis</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Manabu Tokunaga</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Suresh Viswanathan</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n                <h3>Founding Organizations: (alphabetically)</h3>\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Barco</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Lury</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Medken</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Radical Imaging</li>\r\n\r\n                    <li>Raster Images</li>\r\n                </ul>', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-08-12 13:17:33', '2015-08-12 11:17:33', '', 13, 'http://ohif.local/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
